                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.95,
                                "byte_start": 87499,
                                "byte_stop": 123339,
                                "text": "The opinion of the court in No. 00-973, United States versus Vonn will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.95,
                        "stop": 298.318,
                        "byte_start": 123339,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.95,
                                "stop": 15.286,
                                "byte_start": 123339,
                                "byte_stop": 148730,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.286,
                                "stop": 25.736,
                                "byte_start": 148730,
                                "byte_stop": 190526,
                                "text": "Rule 11 of the Federal Rules of Criminal Procedure aims to assure that defendants who plead guilty do so knowingly and voluntarily."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 25.736,
                                "stop": 35.021,
                                "byte_start": 190526,
                                "byte_stop": 227620,
                                "text": "It does this by compelling judges to advice defendants of the nature of the charges against them and the rights they will give up by not going to trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.021,
                                "stop": 42.818,
                                "byte_start": 227620,
                                "byte_stop": 258862,
                                "text": "This advice is known as Rule 11 colloquially and it occurs at the hearing when a defendant pleads guilty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.818,
                                "stop": 60.821,
                                "byte_start": 258862,
                                "byte_stop": 330856,
                                "text": "Rule 11 is unique among the Federal Rules in containing its own review provisions Subsection H, which provides that any error under the Rule that the government can show did not prejudiced the defendant will not affect the validity of the plea."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.821,
                                "stop": 88.187,
                                "byte_start": 330856,
                                "byte_stop": 440257,
                                "text": "Subsection (h) closely tracks the language of Rule 52(a), the Rule\u2019s general harmless-error provision but unlike the General Rule 52, subsection (h) is not accompanied by a plain error provision giving defendants who do not make a timely objection and opportunity to have the error corrected if they can carry the converse burden of showing that the error did not prejudiced them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.187,
                                "stop": 96.456,
                                "byte_start": 440257,
                                "byte_stop": 473380,
                                "text": "In 1977, the respondent, Alphonso Vonn pleaded guilty to three charges arising out of a bank robbery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 96.456,
                                "stop": 119.144,
                                "byte_start": 473380,
                                "byte_stop": 564077,
                                "text": "At two separate plea hearings, the district judge adviced him of the rights he would relinquish by foregoing a trial but the judge felt just short of what Rule 11 requires where he failed to tell Vonn that if he proceeded to trial, he will have the right to counsel at the trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.144,
                                "stop": 130.088,
                                "byte_start": 564077,
                                "byte_stop": 607858,
                                "text": "On appeal Vonn argued for the first time that his guilty pleas on all three counts were invalid because the judge skipped this one item at advice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.088,
                                "stop": 146.356,
                                "byte_start": 607858,
                                "byte_stop": 672955,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit agreed holding that under Rule 11, the government bears the burden of showing that Rule 11 error to the harmless whether or on not the defendant or his lawyer brought that error to the attention of the District Judge in the first place."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.356,
                                "stop": 157.427,
                                "byte_start": 672955,
                                "byte_stop": 717259,
                                "text": "Because the government could not satisfy this burden without making reference to, we advice that Vonn received in proceedings separate from the Rule 11 colloquies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.427,
                                "stop": 160.982,
                                "byte_start": 717259,
                                "byte_stop": 731470,
                                "text": "The Ninth Circuit vacated his guilty pleas."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.982,
                                "stop": 166.116,
                                "byte_start": 731470,
                                "byte_stop": 752054,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the Clerk of the Court, we vacate and remand."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.116,
                                "stop": 189.004,
                                "byte_start": 752054,
                                "byte_stop": 843587,
                                "text": "We hold two things:  first, that a defendant who lets Rule 11 error passed without objection in the trial court must bear the burden in the Court of Appeals of showing prejudice; and second, that the revealing court must look to the entire trial record to make this finding not just the record of the Rule 11 colloquie."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.004,
                                "stop": 199.86,
                                "byte_start": 843587,
                                "byte_stop": 886950,
                                "text": "We reject Vonn\u2019s argument that Congress\u2019 explicit command in Rule 11(h) that harmless-error is to be disregarded."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 199.86,
                                "stop": 207.31,
                                "byte_start": 886950,
                                "byte_stop": 916835,
                                "text": "It was meant to eliminate a defendant\u2019s burden under the Rule 52(b) plain error provision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 207.31,
                                "stop": 225.946,
                                "byte_start": 916835,
                                "byte_stop": 991336,
                                "text": "Although it is a familiar count on the statutory interpretation that the expression of one item in a group of commonly associated items excludes all the others, what evidence of congressional intent there is, here it shows that Congress did not intend so settle a message."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 225.946,
                                "stop": 246.485,
                                "byte_start": 991336,
                                "byte_stop": 1073465,
                                "text": "Rather in enacting Rule 11(h), Congress simply sought to fall a trend that took hold among Courts of Appeals following this court\u2019s decision in the case called McCarthy v. United States, that no Rule 11 slip up no matter how minor could ever be harmless-error."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.485,
                                "stop": 250.863,
                                "byte_start": 1073465,
                                "byte_stop": 1091019,
                                "text": "Rule 11(h) says it can be harmless-error."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 250.863,
                                "stop": 271.772,
                                "byte_start": 1091019,
                                "byte_stop": 1174611,
                                "text": "The Rule that Vonn proposes that the government always has the burden of showing harmlessness, whether or not that error was first brought to the District Judge\u0027s attention, undercuts Congress\u2019 goal evident elsewhere in the Federal Rules that defendants raise any objections to their pleas before sentencing and not afterward."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 271.772,
                                "stop": 283.478,
                                "byte_start": 1174611,
                                "byte_stop": 1221422,
                                "text": "Finally, we find no support for the Ninth Circuit\u2019s Rule that a reviewing court must ignore evidence already on the record but outside the four corners of the plea hearing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 283.478,
                                "stop": 292.249,
                                "byte_start": 1221422,
                                "byte_stop": 1256531,
                                "text": "When the evidence shows that a defendant was not actually harmed by the judge\u2019s failure to comply fully with Rule 11."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 292.249,
                                "stop": 298.318,
                                "byte_start": 1256531,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in part and dissenting in part."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
